       -f, --file-list file_name
              Loads  the  files listed in the specified file. The
              file must contain one name by line. You can specify
              more than one list.

       -h, --help
              Displays the command line options of the editor.

       -k, --use-rh-52-keys
              [[OOnnllyy ffoorr LLiinnuuxx]] Enables the Red Hat 5.2 style key-
              board mapping. That's needed if you are experiment-
              ing  some strange function keys behavior. Some key-
              board mapping files redefines the function key num-
              bers in a good way but really incompatible with the
              old way. I first found it in Red Hat 5.2.

       -K, --keybind file_name
              Uses the specified name  as  keybinding  file.  The
              file  should be full qualified, the editor will use
              this name for reading and writing keyboard configu-
              ration.

