       SET_CMDLINE
              Indicates default command line options. Please read
              the "Passing extra command line options" section of
              the "Miscellaneous" chapter of the manual to under-
              stand how it works.

       SET_FILES
              Indicates  where  the   configuration   files   are
              located.  If  not defined the editor will guess the
              location.

       SET_LOCALEDIR
              Indicates where the internationalization files  for
              the editor are located.

       SET_STACKDBG
              Indicates  the  default  value  for the ----ssttaacckk--ddbbgg
              command line option.

       INFOPATH
              Indicates where  help  files  in  info  format  are
              located.  If  not defined the editor will guess the
              location.

       MANPATH
              The editor uses man command to parse manpages.  For
              this reason MANPATH also affects setedit.

